# Computer Vision Roadmap

## Overview

Future development will introduce computer vision capabilities to improve composition quality, layout intelligence, and automated creative quality control.

The goal is to increase precision, consistency, and adherence to brand standards throughout the composition pipeline.

---

## Hero Image Analysis

Future workflows may first generate a hero image before passing it through a computer vision analysis stage.

This stage may identify:
- Primary focal objects
- Open or negative space
- Composition balance
- Cropping boundaries
- Object positioning
- Visual hierarchy

This structured visual data would then be passed forward into downstream composition agents.

---

## Intelligent Composition Placement

Computer vision outputs may help guide:
- Logo placement
- Typography positioning
- CTA placement
- Brand-safe spacing
- Layout alignment

This would allow the composition agent to make more intelligent and visually balanced layout decisions.

---

## Final Quality Control Pass

Future workflows may include a second computer vision validation pass after composition generation.

This quality-control stage may verify:
- Brand compliance
- Text contrast
- Spacing rules
- Cropping safety
- Color consistency
- Layout alignment

This final validation layer would help ensure assets meet production standards before approval or export.

---

## Deterministic vs Inference-Based Vision

Some computer vision functionality may remain deterministic and rule-based, while other stages may incorporate inference-based AI models.

Potential future approaches may include:
- Object detection
- Segmentation models
- Layout analysis
- AI-assisted composition scoring

Hybrid approaches may be used depending on reliability and performance requirements.
